
@startuml
' Define classes

class ResearchGroup {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -department: Department
}

class Department {
  -id: int
  -name: String
}

class Researcher {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -researchGroup: ResearchGroup
}

class Project {
  -id: int
  -title: String
  -startDate: Date
  -endDate: Date
}

class WorkPackage {
  -id: int
  -title: String
  -project: Project
  -leadingResearchGroup: ResearchGroup
}

class TeamMemberAssignment {
  -id: int
  -researcher: Researcher
  -workPackage: WorkPackage
  -startDate: Date
  -endDate: Date
}

' Define associations

ResearchGroup "1" -- "0..*" Researcher : belongs to
Department "1" -- "0..*" ResearchGroup : contains
Project "1" -- "0..*" WorkPackage : contains
WorkPackage "1" -- "1" ResearchGroup : led by
WorkPackage "0..*" -- "0..*" TeamMemberAssignment : has members
Researcher "0..*" -- "0..*" TeamMemberAssignment : assigned to

' Note: The assignment is re-recorded if researcher or WP leader changes
note right of TeamMemberAssignment
  Service delivery is traceable.
  When a researcher changes group, old assignments are terminated,
  new ones created. Same when WP leadership changes.
end note
@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **ResearchGroup**: A group that belongs to a department and contains researchers.
- **Department**: Contains multiple research groups.
- **Researcher**: Belongs to exactly one research group at any time.
- **Project**: Decomposed into work packages.
- **WorkPackage (WP)**: Part of a project, led by one research group.
- **TeamMemberAssignment**: Records a researcher being assigned to a WP. This is the link that enables tracking of **service delivery** between groups.

### Important Constraints:
- A researcher can be assigned to any WP, regardless of which RG leads it.
- If a researcher changes their group, all existing `TeamMemberAssignment`s are **terminated**, and new ones are created to maintain accurate service delivery records.
- Similarly, if a WP’s leading group changes, team member assignments are re-recorded accordingly.

